results.title: Bihar Elections 2025: How The Young Turks of Bihar Are Trying to Break 'Politisation of Caste'
results.description: Leaders like Tejashwi Yadav, Prashant Kishor, and Kanhaiya Kumar are addressing critical issues like migration and unemployment, appealing particularly to voters aged 18-35. Tejashwi's promise of 10 lakh government jobs resonated with youth during the 2020 elections, while Kishor emphasizes quality education and job creation through his Jan Suraaj Party. Kumar's initiatives also target employment and migration issues.

results.title: US attorney general Pam Bondi fires three Jan 6 Capitol riot prosecutors; letter cites Constitution, offers no specific reason
results.description: The justice department dismissed at least three prosecutors involved in January 6th Capitol riot cases, including supervisors and a line prosecutor. These dismissals, confirmed by anonymous sources, are part of a pattern under the Trump administration raising concerns about political interference. Trump's pardons of January 6th rioters and prior demotions of prosecutors further intensify these fears of retaliation.
